# Canonical Caddyfile for the bag.laugh.town PDS box.
#
# Deployed at /pds/caddy/etc/caddy/Caddyfile (mounted into the `caddy` container
# as /etc/caddy/Caddyfile). This is the source of truth — if you change it on the
# box, mirror it here. To apply a change: edit /pds/caddy/etc/caddy/Caddyfile on
# the box, then `docker exec caddy caddy validate --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile`
# and `docker exec caddy caddy reload --config /etc/caddy/Caddyfile`.
#
# TLS notes (learned the hard way):
# - On-demand TLS is gated by the `ask` endpoint (checkHandleRoute in
#   service/index.ts): it approves the PDS service hostname, hosted user handles
#   (<name>.laugh.town), and the operator hosts in OPERATOR_TLS_HOSTS
#   (admin.laugh.town). A hostname the ask denies gets no cert and fails the TLS
#   handshake with a silent "internal error" (no Caddy log).
# - The on-demand wildcard MUST be `*.laugh.town` (NOT `*.bag.laugh.town`) — user
#   handles are <name>.laugh.town, and handle resolution (bsky.social fetching
#   https://<handle>.laugh.town/.well-known/atproto-did) needs a per-handle cert.
# - `admin.laugh.town` also matches `*.laugh.town`; while that wildcard is a
#   managed on-demand policy, Caddy will NOT serve a *dedicated* managed cert for
#   admin (it gets shadowed and silently serves nothing). So admin.laugh.town
#   carries its own `tls { on_demand }` and is approved by the ask — otherwise its
#   TLS goes dark, taking the admin dashboard AND the atcr deploy webhook
#   (admin.laugh.town/hooks/atcr -> deployer) down with it.

{
	email help@laugh.town
	on_demand_tls {
		ask http://localhost:3000/tls-check
	}
}

*.laugh.town, bag.laugh.town {
	tls {
		on_demand
	}
	reverse_proxy http://localhost:3000
}

admin.laugh.town {
	# Own on-demand tls: admin matches the *.laugh.town wildcard, and a dedicated
	# managed cert gets shadowed by it (serves nothing). On-demand + the ask
	# (checkHandleRoute approves admin.laugh.town) issues and serves it reliably.
	tls {
		on_demand
	}
	# atcr image-push webhook -> deployer (HMAC-verified by the deployer itself).
	handle /hooks/atcr {
		reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8788
	}
	# everything else -> pds-operator admin dashboard.
	handle {
		reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8787
	}
}
